  "issue_number": 116,
  "issue_title": "[Bug]: Kernel emits no decision (fails open) when a code proposal hits an internal error \u2014 unlike the action path which DENYs",
  "issue_body": "### Component\n\nkernel / safety-supervisor (safety layer)\n\n### Description\n\n`KernelService._handle_code_proposal()` swallows internal errors: on any\nexception it logs and returns **without publishing a decision**. The Kernel is\ndocumented as \"the sole authority that may emit a decision\" and must \"fail safe\n(DENY) on internal error\" (CLAUDE.md \u00a73). The sibling `_handle_action_proposal()`\nimplements exactly that \u2014 on exception it publishes a fail-safe DENY\n(`risk_score=1.0`) \"so the caller's Future doesn't hang.\" The code-proposal path\ndoes **not**, so an internal error in the self-modifying-code gate produces\n**no decision at all** instead of a fail-closed DENY.\n\n#### Root cause (code)\n\n`kernel/src/kernel/service.py`, `_handle_code_proposal`:\n\n```python\n        except Exception as e:\n            self.logger.error(f\"Error handling code proposal: {e}\")\n```\n\nCompare `_handle_action_proposal` in the same file:\n\n```python\n        except Exception as e:\n            self.logger.error(f\"Error handling action proposal: {e}\")\n            # Always publish a decision so the caller's Future doesn't hang.\n            # Fail-safe: DENY on internal errors.\n            try:\n                deny = KernelDecision(\n                    trace_id=trace_id, type=DecisionType.DENY,\n                    reason=f\"Kernel internal error: {e}\", risk_score=1.0,\n                )\n                await self._publish_and_log_decision(trace_id, proposal_type, source, deny)\n                self._deny_count += 1\n            except Exception:\n                pass  # best-effort \u2014 caller will timeout\n```\n\nThe action handler emits a fail-safe DENY; the code handler emits nothing.\n\n#### Why it matters\n\nThe Meta-Programmer publishes `code.proposal` and waits for a decision on\n`code_decision_subject(trace_id)`. If `_get_risk_analysis`,\n`evaluate_code_proposal`, `_log_decision`, or the publish raises, the Kernel\nemits no decision on that subject. The self-modifying-code path is the most\nsafety-sensitive one in the system (the Meta-Programmer may \"only deploy code\nthe Kernel approved\"), yet here the Kernel \u2014 by its own documented contract the\nsole decision authority that must fail closed \u2014 stays silent on internal error.\nThe end state then depends entirely on the consumer's timeout behavior rather\nthan on the Kernel affirmatively denying, and it is asymmetric with the action\npath that already does the right thing.\n\n### Steps to Reproduce\n\nDrive the handler with an evaluator that raises (mirrors an internal error), via\na fake event bus:\n\n```python\nimport asyncio, logging\nfrom activelearning import KernelDecisionType as DecisionType\nfrom activelearning.subjects import code_decision_subject\nfrom kernel.service import KernelService\n\nclass FakeBus:\n    def __init__(self): self.published = []\n    async def publish(self, subject, payload): self.published.append((subject, payload))\n\nsvc = KernelService.__new__(KernelService)        # bypass __init__ (no NATS/DB)\nsvc.logger = logging.getLogger(\"t\"); svc._deny_count = 0\nsvc._evaluator = type(\"E\", (), {\"evaluate_code_proposal\": lambda *a, **k: (_ for _ in ()).throw(RuntimeError(\"boom\"))})()\nsvc.event_bus = FakeBus()\nasync def _none(*a, **k): return None\nsvc._get_risk_analysis = _none; svc._log_decision = _none\n\nasyncio.run(svc._handle_code_proposal({\"trace_id\": \"t1\", \"source\": \"meta-programmer\"}))\nprint(\"published:\", svc.event_bus.published)\n```\n\n### Expected Behavior\n\nOn an internal error the Kernel publishes a fail-safe **DENY** on\n`code_decision_subject(\"t1\")` (`risk_score=1.0`), mirroring the action path:\n\n```\npublished: [('decision.code.t1', {'trace_id': 't1', 'type': 'DENY', 'risk_score': 1.0, ...})]\n```\n\n### Actual Behavior\n\n```shell\npublished: []\n```\n\nNo decision is published \u2014 the Kernel fails open (silent) on the\nself-modifying-code path instead of failing closed with a DENY.\n\n### Environment\n\n- OS: Windows 10 (platform-independent \u2014 pure Python control flow)\n- Python: 3.11 / 3.12\n- Run mode: any (`python run.py` or Docker)\n- Commit: `dev` @ latest\n\n---\n\n#### Suggested fix (for discussion)\n\nMirror `_handle_action_proposal`: hoist `trace_id`/`source` out of the `try`, and\nin the `except` publish a signed fail-safe DENY to `code_decision_subject(trace_id)`\n(`risk_score=1.0`) inside a best-effort inner `try`. A regression test asserting a\nDENY is published when evaluation raises would lock it in. Happy to open a PR.\n\n### Pre-submission checks\n\n- [x] I searched existing issues and this is not a duplicate.\n- [x] I am running the latest `dev`.",
